Dating: NEW KINGDOM (not before); NEW KINGDOM ?; LATE PERIOD (not after)
Name: Anepigraphic canopic jar
Description: This canopic jar of alabaster was part of the G. Hagemans collection. It is equipped with a lid in the form of a canine's head. In view of the absence of any inscription or of any other information concerning the provenance, it is impossible to put forward a precise date.
